The contingent of 43-strong, under French coach Franck Dumas, will hold their first training session in the country Monday at Moi Sports Centre, Kasarani and have feel of Nyayo Stadium on Tuesday.In the squad are midfielder Amir Sayoud, who bagged a hat-trick in Algiers together with the other scorers in that match Hamza Bellahouel, winger Larbi Tabti and striker Maecky Ngombo. Frantic efforts were made Sunday to convince Gor Mahia players to return to training for their Champions League first round second leg match against Algeria’s CR Belouizdad.
The match is scheduled for Wednesday at Nyayo National Stadium, but it remains to be seen whether the disgruntled players, agitating to be paid two months salary arrears, will honour the fixture.



