Gor lost the first leg 6-0 on Boxing Day in Algeria and, realistically, can only advance if a miracle were to occur.
Only 10 players showed up for training Sunday under Posta Rangers coach Sammy Omollo, who is helping out at the club in the absence of a Caf certified tactician.
Gor Mahia team manager Jolawi Obondo told Nation Sport that every effort was being made to get all the players in training and he expected a full house Monday.



